Nine men accused of gang raping a 13-year-old girl in Nyanga submitted affidavits to court yesterday to motivate why they should be released on bail.The affidavits were handed in at the Wynberg Magistrate&rsquo;s Court.&nbsp;The State was expected to respond to their bail application on February 1.The men are accused of repeatedly raping a 13-year-old girl in a shack in Nyanga on November 11.Police said the teenager had been walking alone on Robert Sobukwe Road around 20:00 when a man abducted her. He took her to a shack where he and his friends repeatedly raped her.She was held overnight and released the next day.The ninth man was arrested last week after returning to the province from a long stint in the Eastern Cape.His co-accused are aged between 18 and 20.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/nine-men-accused-of-raping-nyanga-teen-apply-for-bail-20170127